What is PyTest?
PyTest is an open-source testing framework for Python, designed to make it easy to write simple and scalable test cases for your code.

Key Features
Simple Syntax: Easy-to-write and read test cases.
Fixtures: Reusable setup and teardown code.
Plugins: Extendable with a rich ecosystem of plugins.
Parameterization: Run tests with multiple sets of parameters.
Advantages
Open Source
User-Friendly
Highly Extendable
Supports Various Test Types (unit, functional, integration)
Strong Community Support
Use Cases
Unit Testing
Integration Testing
Functional Testing
End-to-End Testing
